13/03/2008
BUCHAREST, Romania -- The government approved on Wednesday (March 12th) the date of June 1st for the first round of local elections. The second round will be held on June 15th. Candidates have between March 31st and April 22nd to register, and campaigning is set to start on May 2nd. 
Also Wednesday, Secretary-General Ilie Bolojan resigned in order to run for mayor of the town of Oreada. He will stay on until a replacement is found. (Nine o'clock - 13/03/08; Mediafax, Hotnews.ro - 12/03/08)
